I am now officially literate, so I will proceed to explain what
each symbol does. 
If you are not yet literate, 
do not read the following, 
doing so would ruin the fun:
The dot changes the symbols directly next to it.
The square with dots around it transform the symbol to its right into 
the one to its left.
The crosshair changes the symbol in its opposite position.
The pillar with three dots changes all the symbols between it and 
its nearest edge. 
The three lines with a dot change the symbol to its nearest edge and 
the symbol in the opposite direction that is equidistant from it as
its nearest edge.
The square with two triangles and two dots is a little difficult to 
explain, but if you number the positions from one to eight,
if this symbol is in position 1, then it will change position 5. 
So, 1#5, then the pattern is... 
1#5
2#1
3#6
4#2
5#7
